Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and sprinkle over
the @Chinese Five Spice{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @slow cooked British pork{425%g} from the packaging. Place
in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices and cover loosely with #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf for ~{25-30%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is
piping hot throughout.

While everything's in the oven, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2}(sliced
as thinly as you can).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the sliced onion, @rice vinegar{15%ml} and
@sugar for the pickle{1%tsp}.

Add a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside to pickle.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Sriracha sauce{15%g} and half the
@mayonnaise{96%g}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and toss until evenly coated. Set aside.

Once cooked, remove the pork from the oven, then discard the foil and any
cooking juices.

Use two #forks{} to shred the pork as finely as you can.

Stir the @teriyaki sauce{75%g} and @soy sauce{25%ml} through the pork. Taste
and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{3.96} (2 per person) onto a baking tray and into
the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, lay the warmed tortillas onto your #plates{}.

Spread the remaining mayo over the tacos using the back of a #spoon{}. Top with
the pulled pork and a few slices of pickled onion - as much as you'd like.

Add the remaining pickled onion along with any liquids to the slaw. Toss to
combine.

Serve the tacos with the fries and sriracha slaw on the side. TIP: Tacos are
best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!

Enjoy!